rthern Europe. The practice of depicting from life became a self-conscious departure from the norms of Italian arts. In the context of court culture in Rome and Florence, works by artists ranging from Caravaggio to Claude Lorrain, Pieter van Laer to Jacques Callot, reveal new aspects of their artistic practice and its critical implications.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aArt, Europeany17th century. 0aArt, Italiany17th century. 0aPortrait drawing, ItalianxHistoryy17th century. 0aPortrait painting, ItalianxHistoryy17th century. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aCultural Studies. 4aEarly Modern Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 7aART / European.2bisacsh  aBamboccianti.  aCaraavaggio.  aClaude Lorrain.  aJacques Callot.  aad vivum.  arealism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertArt and Architecture eBook-Package 2020z978311073823008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2020z9783110704679oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishz978311070478508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048533268?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048533268423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048533268/original  a